! ASSERT_CONVENTION: natural_units=explicit_hbar_kB, fourier_convention=QE_planewave
!
! HgBa2Ca2Cu3O8+delta (Hg1223) -- q2r.x input
!
! Converts dynamical matrices from reciprocal space (DFPT q-grid)
! to real-space interatomic force constants (IFCs).
!
! Prerequisite: completed ph.x run (all q-points in hg1223.dyn0..dynN)
!
! The acoustic sum rule (asr='crystal') is enforced to ensure:
!   - Three acoustic branches go to exactly zero at Gamma
!   - Translational invariance is satisfied
!   - Small numerical violations from DFPT are corrected

&INPUT
  fildyn = 'hg1223.dyn'
  zasr   = 'crystal'
  flfrc  = 'hg1223.fc'
/

! OUTPUT:
!   hg1223.fc  -- real-space interatomic force constants
!                 This file is input for matdyn.x (phonon interpolation)
!                 and for EPW (electron-phonon coupling)
!
! NOTES:
!   zasr = 'crystal' is appropriate for 3D periodic crystals.
!   For 2D or molecular systems, use 'simple' or 'one-dim'.
!   'crystal' enforces the full crystal ASR including the invariance
!   under rigid rotations (important for layered structures like Hg1223
!   where the c-axis acoustic mode can have numerical noise).
